description:
Kaalamang Pangkalusugan
with Doc Tam Mateo & Gladense Panuelos
Kaalamang Pangkalusugan  | Episode 46: Physical Activity

chapters.title: Hang loose. During your bus or train trip, stand and don't hold on too tightly. You'll improve your sense of balance and build up your "core" back and abdominal muscles.
Walk tall. Maintaining good posture - chest out, shoulders square but relaxed, stomach in - wil help keep your back and abdominal muscles in shape
Get into the swing of it. Swinging your arms when you walk wil help you reach the brisk pace of 3 to 4 miles per hour that is the most healthful.
Adopt someone as your walking, jogging, or biking buddy. Adding a social element to exercise helps many people stick with it.
That buddy might have four legs. Several studies have shown that dog owners get more exercise than the canine-less.
Be part of the fun. Adults shouldn't miss a chance to jump into the fray if kids are playing on a playground or splashing around in the water. Swinging on a swing will strengthen muscles and bones.

Clean house. Even if you have a cleaning service, you can take responsibility for vacuuming a couple of rooms yourself. Fifteen minutes burns around 80 calories. Wash some windows and do some dusling and you've got a pretty decent workout and a cleaner house.
Hide that remote. Channel surfing can add hours to screen time. If you have to get up to change the channel. you are more likely to turn it off and maybe do something else that's less sedentary

every organ and function must be in perfect operation as God designed they should be. If all the organs act their natural part, life, health, and happiness, will be the result. Too little exercise, and staying in-doors too much, will bring on feebleness and disease of some one or more of the organs.
